From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Codex <codex@openai.com>
Date: Wed, 17 Jun 2026 00:00:00 -0700
Subject: [PATCH] arm64: dts: mediatek: mt7988a-bpi-r4-pro-8x: add Wi-Fi
 EEPROM

The BPI-R4 Pro 8X schematic shows one AT24C02-compatible EEPROM for the
Wi-Fi card on channel 3 of the PCA9545 I2C mux at address 0x51.

Describe only the EEPROM device itself. Do not use it as the mt7996
calibration EEPROM source: mt7996 expects a full 7680-byte EEPROM image,
while this device is a 256-byte AT24C02. MAC address and calibration
offsets still need runtime validation.
---
 arch/arm64/boot/dts/mediatek/mt7988a-bananapi-bpi-r4-pro.dtsi | 8 ++++++++
 1 file changed, 8 insertions(+)

--- a/arch/arm64/boot/dts/mediatek/mt7988a-bananapi-bpi-r4-pro.dtsi
+++ b/arch/arm64/boot/dts/mediatek/mt7988a-bananapi-bpi-r4-pro.dtsi
@@ -445,6 +445,14 @@
 		imux3_wifi: i2c@3 {
 			reg = <3>;
 			#address-cells = <1>;
 			#size-cells = <0>;
+
+			wifi_eeprom: eeprom@51 {
+				compatible = "atmel,24c02";
+				reg = <0x51>;
+				address-width = <8>;
+				pagesize = <8>;
+				size = <256>;
+			};
 		};
 	};
 };
